Even with their intense and ongoing training, advanced weapons and armor tech, and significant support from fleet assets and otherwise, mortality rates are high for these troopers as they fight off the encroaching Sith Empire as the very tip of the spear.

Sergeant Nahulu is a fervently loyal soldier of the Republic, and one of the first few to have enlisted under the Special Forces Scheme. He has a peculiar loathing for traitors and defectors, and rumors have it that he had neutralized more than one such defector before in his time in service, though he does not speak much of such.

"These gardens were here before we were, and mayhaps when peace finally dawns upon our Galactic Republic, we shall leave Viscara with these gardens unscathed. As before we were here, so may it remain after our watch is over, and we may depart. In the meantime, let it be a reminder of what we fight for, these gardens of peace.

-- Captain Tyche Vanicus"

Atop a pole flies proudly the flag of the Galactic Republic. Soldiers of Outpost Hope have duty rotations to guard it, and tiring and these duties are, they were considered an honorable posting. Bannerguards are expected to be unflinching in their defence of the flag, and are rewarded with extra hours off and rest after each proud rotation.

This worn and weathered stone sits within the memorial garden. Words have been painstakingly carved upon it, and it appears maintained with a surprising care, despite within a military base. Upon this stone are scribed these words:

"In this age of war, we burn our lives for a peace we may never see. From your failing hands to ours, we shall raise the torch of your hope, that your light may never be extinguished. We shall remember you and your final sacrifice.

...

... a list of names follow...

... Captain Thornton...

... Rodi Lucce...

..."
